page.title: 19N.Upottery:Our birds
page.content: Our two most spectacular birds are the buzzards and the herons.The latter can sometimes be seen along the Otter and the buzzards often hang high overhead.They have their nest in a small tree in a copse in this part of the valley. Other birds seen in the area are: Pheasant Redwing Chaffinch Dove Tits,blue,coal, Brambling Pigeon willow,great, Jay Swallow longtailed. Sparrow Martin Nuthatch Wren Wagtail Treecreeper Dipper Yellowhammer Kingfisher Dunnock Kingfisher Greenfinch Magpie Robin Jackdaw Starling Blackbird Rook Thrush Spotted woodpecker
